sql:
SELECT AVG(total_amount) AS average_order_value
FROM (
  SELECT p.ord_id, SUM(p.amount) AS total_amount
  FROM payments p
  GROUP BY p.ord_id
) AS total_orders;

external_knowledge:
- "Planted seeds" refers to the quantity of products ordered;
- "Type of product" refers to the product name;
- "Stores" refers to the store names.

sql:
SELECT title_name, stock_qty 
FROM inventory 
ORDER BY stock_qty DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "golden order types" refers to the most lucrative or highest-revenue-generating order types;
- "bring in the most revenue" indicates the order types with the highest total payment amounts;
- The query ranks order types by total payment amount in descending order and selects the top-ranked one for each store and date.

- 'Most loyal customers' refers to customers who have placed the most orders at each store;
- 'Shipping speed' is categorized as 'Fast' (less than 3 days), 'Medium' (3 to 7 days), and 'Slow' (more than 7 days);
- 'Total revenue' is the sum of all payments made to the store.
